The princess reaches the end of the river crossing,
and finds an unconcious girl on the ground.
\n<\n[2]>Wait, do you feel that?
\n<\n[1]>What? I don't have your weird paladin-ey
senses, ya know?
\n<\n[2]>Behind us!
A
\n<Mayor>Well, thanks for the help there, that
bloody thing jumped me earlier when the
storm hit, it didn't seem to mind it, but
I was a sitting duck.
\n<\n[2]>Seems like the storm has caused problems
all over the place.
\n<\n[1]>Well, that's what we're here for!
\n<Mayor>If there's anything I can do, let me
know.
\n<\n[1]>Well, we came here looking for the mayor
of Castletown. Are they here? The lady at
the crystal sent us to this weird place
to find them.
\n<Mayor>Oh, well, I'm the mayor. I come out here
regularly, it just happened at a bad time
I guess.
\n<\n[1]>Well, that's convenient. We're checking out
the kingdom to see how the storm's affected everyone,
and we heard you were caught out here in it.
People1
Well, since you saved me, I suppose I can
trust you. Here, this key will open the
crystal gate. You can check how it held up.
We kept it secure after a recent incident.
TinyGetInfoWnd item 17
\n<\n[2]>If you don't mind me asking, what incident?
I'm with the Leonis Royal Guard, it's my
job to keep up with events like this, it
may help with our investigations.
\n<Mayor>Royal Guard..? Hey, wait, I knew you looked
familiar, I'm surprised I didn't recognize
you sooner, you're the princess' bodyguard!
And you must be...?
\n<\n[1]>Yep, that's me. No need for formality
though, I don't really like all that stuff.
I'm just out here to help the people, I
don't need any special treatment.
\n<Mayor>Exactly as the rumours say, the people's
princess. I'm glad you live up to the
reputation. Alright then, I'll tell you
what happened.
\n<Mayor>About a week ago, some strange man came
in to town, we thought he was just a
visitor from the Frontiers who hadn't seen
civilized kingdom life before, but there
\n<Mayor>was something... off... about him.
\n<\n[2]>How so?
\n<Mayor>He felt... weird? His eyes looked empty,
you could just feel magical energy from
him, and the weather turned bad right as he
entered town.
\n<\n[1]>I don't get it, there's plenty of weird
folk around the kingdom, why'd you need to
protect the crystal?
\n<Mayor>Because he started casting some strange
spell on it, the crystal visibly started
going darker while he chanted his spell,
and naturally since we rely on the
\n<Mayor>crystals magic, the guard's noticed and
ran the guy out of town. But just in case,
we set up the gate around it after that,
and only I have the key.
\n<\n[2]>I see... But, if only you have the key,
who is the woman that was inside the gate?
People1
I have no idea. Nobody should be in there.
\n<\n[1]>Well, we'll head back now. You going to be
alright here?
\n<Mayor>Yeah, I'll be fine, now that monster has
been dealt with and the storms gone here,
I shouldn't have any problems, I know this
area pretty well.
And so, the princess saves the day, and now makes her
way back to town to report in her success.
